content.description: Sit start near the far left side of the mini roof. Feet to the left and right with matching hands on the hold above. High right crimp, and mantle up. Go straight up from there.
content.location: The large Northwest face of carthage. Middle to the left sit start.

content.description:
Carthage boulder has a North West face that is roughly 9ish feet of conglomerate concerte and paint. For houston, it's something to climb. Sharp rock and half rotten so make sure you bring tape and a good pad.

 If anyone has any prior ascents or any name changes needed, please let me know so I can update the page.
